<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13516] Increase PermSize to 128MB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13516</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HBase uses ~40MB, and with Phoenix we use ~56MB of Perm space out of 64MB by default. Every Filter and Coprocessor increases that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running out of perm space triggers a stop the world full GC of the entire heap. We have seen this in misconfigured cluster. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should we default to  &lt;tt&gt;-XX:PermSize=128m -XX:MaxPermSize=128m&lt;/tt&gt; out of the box as a convenience for users? &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
